text.tspan: Multidrug-resistant tuberculosis without extensive drug resistance,
Incidence refers to the number of new tuberculosis infections whereas prevalence is the number of people living with tuberculosis.
Included are infections at any age and of both sexes.
Data source: IHME, Global Burden of Disease (2019)
